How admirable these dispositions, but how still more ad- mirable their operation and results! The word of a bishop goes forth. It is taken up and repeated by a zealous and united clergy to their faithful flocks through the length and breadth of an entire diocese. It finds a response in every breast ; and all are animated with a common sentiment, feeling that the demand is on the part of the Almighty. A tribute is set on foot, every one contributin g according to his means, even to the widow, who, from her poverty, gives her humble mite.
